raceComments: {"comment":"5. HE'LL RIP was back in winning form at Flemington nearly 5 weeks ago, scoring comfortably by nearly 2 lengths. He has been kept up to the mark with a jumpout since then, and he has won on this circuit in the past. A repeat effort will take him close to winning again. 3. CATOGGIO ran out of condition late, fresh up at Flemington in the same race as the top pick, and has also had a jumpout since then. He proved as a 3-year-old that he is up to this level, and with that run under his belt, he could be hard to get past here. 12. INNCOURT has been racing well in Sydney, winning his last start at Warwick Farm. His trainer would not have trekked all this way just for the scenery. 1. ANGLAND needed his first run back from a spell, and should not be risked here. Include in all combinations.","runners":[5,3,12,1],"exclusive":true}
